Title: Beethoven Symphony No 6 F major Pastoral Franz Wesler Möst London Philharmonic
Description:
Ludwig van Beethoven 
Sinfonie Nr. 6 F-Dur op. 68 Pastoral Symphony No 6 F major 
Kurt Masur conducts Leipzig Gewandhaus Orchestra 1989
1.Erwachen heiterer Empfindungen bei der Ankunft auf dem Lande (Awakening of cheerful feelings upon arrival in the country): Allegro ma non troppo 0:00
2.Szene am Bach (Scene at the brook): Andante molto mosso 9:23
3.Lustiges Zusammensein der Landleute (Happy gathering of country folk): Allegro 22:08
4.Gewitter, Sturm (Thunderstorm; Storm): Allegro 27:12
5.Hirtengesang. Frohe und dankbare Gefühle nach dem Sturm (Shepherds' song; cheerful and thankful feelings after the storm): Allegretto 30:47

Title: Tchaikovsky 5th Symphony - Gustav Mahler Jugendorchester
Description:
(1) 0:00 - (2) 13:51 - (3) 27:00 - (4) 32:45
Gustav Mahler Jugendorchester, Franz Welser-Möst, Vienna Musikverein (19.9.2009)

0:00 - 1. Andante - Allegro con anima (E minor) 
13:51 - 2. Andante cantabile, con alcuna licenza - Moderato con anima - Andante mosso - Allegro non troppo (D major)
27:00 - 3. Valse: Allegro moderato (A major)
32:45 - 4. Finale: Andante maestoso — Allegro vivace — Molto vivace — Moderato assai e molto maestoso - Presto (E major, E minor, E major)
--
The Symphony No. 5 in E minor, Op. 64 by Pyotr Ilyich Tchaikovsky was composed between May and August 1888 and was first performed in St Petersburg at the Hall of Nobility on November 6 of that year with Tchaikovsky conducting.
